Mexican Stocks: Asur, Geo Decline; Elektra, Penoles Advance

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-02-21T23:38:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/mexican-stocks-elektra-penoles-wal-mart-de-mexico-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 0.8 percent to 37,242.05.  Corp. GEO SAB (GEOB MM), Mexico’s second-largest
homebuilder, plunged 6 percent to 34.21 pesos. The company had
its recommendation cut to “hold” from “buy” at Deutsche Bank
AG. JPMorgan Chase & Co. cut the homebuilder’s rating on Feb.
19, citing its debt and revenue growth that missed estimates.  Gruma SAB (GRUMAB MM) fell for a sixth day after the
company completed the sale of its stake in Grupo Financiero
Banorte SAB. The tortilla maker fell 2 percent to 24.61 pesos.  Grupo Aeroportuario del Sureste SAB (ASURB MM), the
operator of airports in southern Mexico, dropped 3.2 percent to
63.11 pesos. Oil surged to the highest in more than two years as  Libya  erupted into violence, signaling higher fuel prices that
may curb  air travel .  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, gained 1.3 percent to 415.15 pesos. Silver
reached a 30-year high as unrest in the Middle East and concern
inflation will quicken boosted demand for precious metals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
